==English==

===Adjective===

'''sacrosanct'''



1. extremely sacred or inviolable: <I>a sacrosanct chamber in the temple.<I>  
2. not to be entered or trespassed upon: <I>She considered her home office sacrosanct.<I>  
3. above or beyond criticism, change, or interference: <I>a manuscript deemed sacrosanct.  


